        "name": "Ravening Maw",
        "desc": "Zevgavizeb's unceasing hunger has been inflicted upon you. You become overwhelmed with cannibalistic hunger and can restore your vitality by feasting on the flesh of the fallen. On your turn, you can use 2 actions (these actions have the manipulate trait) to cannibalize an adjacent dying or dead creature. If the cannibalized creature is dying, it dies. If the cannibalized creature is your ally, you regain |dice=var1| <var>var1</var> HP; otherwise, you regain |dice=var2| <var>var2</var> HP. Certain monsters (such as those whose blood is acidic or magical) might inflict additional effects on you when you cannibalize them, at the GM's discretion. Once cannibalized, a particular creature's body doesn't have enough meat to cannibalize again. During any round that there's a dying or dead creature within 30 feet of you, if you can't or don't cannibalize a creature, you take |dice=var3 Mental| <var>var3</var> mental damage.",
